            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> You need to use `vim.api.nvim_feedkeys(vim.api.nvim_replace_termcodes('<Esc>', false, true, true), 'nx', false)`. You may also need to set `vim.o.showmode = false`.\n\nAdding that before the inspect() call, works. `feedkeys(..., 'nx')` is the general practice to execute input immediately.\n\n> the issue is that I can't get selection information from within the mapping while in visual mode\n\n`getregionpos()` can be used for this now.\n\n```lua\nvim.keymap.set({'v'}, '<space><space>', function()\n  print(vim.inspect{\n      vim.fn.mode(),\n      vim.fn.getregionpos(vim.fn.getpos('v'), vim.fn.getpos('.'), { type='v' })\n  })\nend, { silent = true })\n```\n\n\n\n# Proposal\n\nIt might be useful if `interrupt()` accepted a flag that made it useful in more situations, like this.",
